result.title: 2006 - 2006 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) Survey : CEND 8/06 (part of South Western Beam Trawl Survey, Qtr 1 (FSS: Q1SWBEAM))
result.name: 2006-2006-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-survey-cend-8-06-part-of-s
result.notes:
This survey was undertaken by Cefas as part of the South Western Beam Trawl 
Survey, Qtr 1 (FSS: Q1SWBEAM);

Annual research vessel surveys in the Western English Channel using 4m beam 
trawls in support of EU data regulations and as part of an ICES funded 
research program. Randomly selected survey position design. In 2012 the survey 
coverage was extended to cover the Celtic Sea using both the 4m beam trawl and 
the GOV trawl. In 2013 the survey returned to using the 4m beam trawl only. 
Additional aims include collection of benthic, water temperature and salinity 
and acoustic data.

Survey took place between 21/03/2006 and 04/04/2006 on CEFAS Endeavour

Equipment used during this survey :


-   No Blinder Starboard deployed Beam Trawl 4m steel commericial with 
    extended codend
-   Port deployed Beam Trawl 4m steel commericial with extended codend

Survey operations were undertaken on 80 stations

207 different species were caught on this survey
